#PID Server Readme

##Introduction

Simple implementation of a PID controller for the Raspberry PI. The Parameters of the PID controller can be set via a Webpage


## Requirements

*Python 3
*Python USBTMC (install usbtmc as explained in the readme found in 
in the python_usbtmc_master folder)


## Installation

Find the Vendor and Product ID of the USB-Device used and convert the Values to decimal.
Change the values in Line 29 of PID_server.py to the Values of your device.

To run the PID controller open the Terminal and move to this directory and type

>> python3 PID_Server.py




The Page to set the parameters can be found at:

127.0.0.1:5000/setup
or via LAN at:
